data.title: International Jazz Collections
data.meta_description: Item from International Jazz Collections: Ella Fitzgerald was a jazz vocalist. This collection was assembled with materials acquired by the University of Idaho and donated to the Library in 1997....
data.text: The International Jazz Collections (IJC) is the leading jazz archive in the Pacific Northwest. It features papers, photographs, audio/visual materials, and artifacts from jazz legends such as Lionel Hampton, Leonard Feather, Lee Morse, Dizzy Gillespie, and Ella Fitzgerald.
